<task id="R3-061" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Schema migration — `sprk_searchindexed` → `sprk_searchindexqueuedon` + `sprk_searchindexcompletedon`</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
Host entity CONFIRMED as `sprk_document` via inventory (task 060 notes §2A) and cross-checked against
`Spaarke.Dataverse.DataverseWebApiService._entitySetName = "sprk_documents"` (line 27) and
`Models.cs DocumentEntity` (line 193) which holds the `SearchIndexed` property mapping to
`sprk_searchindexed` (lines 177, 286).

Deployed `scripts/Migrate-SprkSearchIndexedSchema.ps1` (NEW — idempotent, mirrors the
R3-015 `Create-BackgroundJobEntity.ps1` pattern) to spaarkedev1. First run:
  - sprk_searchindexqueuedon    : CREATED (DateTime, DateAndTime, UserLocal)
  - sprk_searchindexcompletedon : CREATED (DateTime, DateAndTime, UserLocal)
  - sprk_searchindexed          : PRESERVED (legacy bool — dual-write transition per spec line 366)
  - sprk_searchindexedon        : PRESERVED (sibling legacy datetime; informational)
  - PublishXml: OK
  - Final verification: all 4 attributes present.

Idempotency PROVEN — second run produced `Skipped: sprk_searchindexqueuedon, sprk_searchindexcompletedon`
with `Created: (none)` and legacy field still PRESENT.

Authored new data-model doc `docs/data-model/sprk_document-search-index-lifecycle.md` covering
the migration rationale, the dual-write contract, the lifecycle semantics (enqueued vs completed),
and the post-R3 drop path. Updated `docs/data-model/sprk_financial-related-entities.md` catalog:
added 2 new rows for the new datetime fields (alphabetical insert between sprk_searchindexedon
and sprk_searchindexname), and annotated both legacy fields (sprk_searchindexed,
sprk_searchindexedon) as "Legacy — preserved for dual-write transition".

DEVIATION from spec/POML reference: the POML originally cited `DeliverToIndexNodeExecutor.cs` as
the dual-write site. Per inventory finding §6.3, that file does NOT currently contain
`sprk_searchindexed` references. Task 062 will instead apply dual-write at the
**Spaarke.Dataverse mapping layer** (`DataverseWebApiService` + `DataverseServiceClientImpl`)
per inventory recommendation §6.2 — single choke-point covers all 3 upstream writers
(RagIndexingJobHandler, RagEndpoints.IndexFile, RagEndpoints.SendToIndex) with zero call-site churn.

This task is schema-only — no BFF code change, no NFR-01 size delta, no CVE surface change.
Removal of the legacy `sprk_searchindexed` is explicitly DEFERRED to a future R4 task per spec
assumption (line 366) and is NOT part of R3 scope.
